OL,4,Csecretary in Eluned Morgan's cabinet
OL,6,FPlaid Cymru leader Rhun ap Iorwerth
OL,7,Fsaid: "Whilst Plaid Cymru MSs didn't
OL,8,Fvote for her, yesterday I wished the
OL,9,Fnew first minister well in trying to
OL,10,Fgrapple with issues that Labour have
OL,11,Fso far failed to address.
OL,13,F"But it's concerning that what we see
OL,14,Fyet again today is evidence that
OL,15,FEluned Morgan means 'no change'. She
OL,16,Fhasn't described her own vision, she's
OL,17,Fkept the cabinet as it was, pretty
OL,18,Fmuch, and even where change was forced
OL,19,Fin her, as she leaves health to take
OL,20,Fon the top job, we get only an interim
OL,21,Fappointment.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/9
